Second-placed Sporting failed to keep up the  pressure on leaders Benfica and were beaten 2-1 at Maritimo Funchal Friday  night. The defeat leaves Sporting three points behind Benfica who have 49  points and a game in hand.
Friday's first division result in Portugal:
Maritimo Funchal 2 (Jose Pedro 26, Humberto 83) Sporting Lisbon 1 (Cadete  52)
